'''KLO''' is a news/talk radio station broadcasting out of [[Ogden, Utah]] to the [[Salt Lake City]] area. The stations airs syndicated conservative talk shows, including [[Bill Bennett]], [[Laura Ingraham]], [[Michael Medved]], and [[Dennis Prager]]. When startup [[KFMS|97.5 FM Talk]] changed its format in late 2006, KLO added [[Michael Savage (commentator)|Michael Savage]] and [[Bill O'Reilly (commentator)|Bill O'Reilly]], who had previously been a part of their lineup. KLO's [[skywave]] signal has been heard as far away as [[Casa Grande, Arizona]] at night.

==History==
[[Image:KLOtowers.jpg|thumb|left|The radio towers for KLO 1430, near [[Clearfield, Utah]].]]
KLO originally signed on in the mid-20s as [[KFUR]]. Its current calls came about in the 1930s in honor of Mt. Lomond located near Ogden. KLO was the flagship of the [[Interstate Broadcasting Corporation]], later the [[Intermountain Network]].<ref>[http://www.oldradio.com/archives/stations/slc-hist.htm Salt Lake Broadcasting History]</ref>

